I think the easiest solution would be to add this css ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/ays5obwt/17/)): 

```css
select, option {
  text-transform: capitalize;
}
```

Or, if you want to change this internally - *your users will have to pay attention to case* - you would change both the [`ignoreCase`](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#ignorecase) and [`filter_ignoreCase`](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#widget-filter-ignorecase) options to `false` ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/ays5obwt/18/)).

I ended up copying some of the changes you have in the refactoring, but I didn't add the groupers method you included... to me, it seems more complex than the original method. If I wanted to add `text` grouping ([already added](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-grouping.html#header_class_names)), all I would need to do is include this code:

```js
$.tablesorter.grouping.types.text = function( config, $column, txt ) {
  return txt;
};
```

Then use "group-text" in the header.

