@xoviat I spent some time with this last night, and there are a couple problems with that.
One is that operators can't apply to specifiers, only clauses (e.g. `!(!A,!B)` - `!()` isn't a thing AFAIK).
Another is negating the compatible release operator. `~= V.N` is the same as `>= V.N, == V.*`, which can technically be negated, but De Morgan re-introduces the OR: `!(< V.N | != V.*)`.

