My point about ditching the export loop in favor of recursion is that I've always approached the loop with a touch of fear. It also seemed like that should instead be a `.export` method like:

```python
class StringType(object):
    def export(self):
        return repr(self)

class ListType(object):
    def export(self):
        return [child.export() for child in self.children]
```

