@laukaching This is an interesting an I imagine common problem. For image classification, if you only train on cats and dogs and you show it an image where neither a cat nog a dog is present, then you are sort of breaking the promise that you made during training about the statistics of the data.

If you want to be able to make reasonable evaluations on non-cat-dog images, then I suggest introducing a third "other" class and make sure it is represented during training. Any images do, as long as they don't have cats and dogs in them. If they are close to the data that your model might see in actual use, that is the ideal.

This is a subtle but I imagine common issue and could be good to mention in the documentation. I'll add a docs tag to this issue.

